# This file lets GitHub render a "Cite this repository" button and lets
# reference managers (Zotero, etc.) import a citation. Schema docs:
# https://citation-file-format.github.io/
cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Lean Pool"
message: >-
  If you use Lean Pool, please cite it using the metadata in this file.
  If you build on a specific formalization in the pool, please also cite
  that project's original authors and source, which are recorded in
  LeanPool/projects.yml, the NOTICE file, and the per-file headers.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Vasily
    family-names: Ilin
    # orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000"   # TODO: add if available
    # affiliation: ""                                   # TODO: add if desired
  - given-names: Justin
    family-names: Asher
    # orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000"   # TODO: add if available
    # affiliation: ""                                   # TODO: add if desired
abstract: >-
  Lean Pool is a curated archive of Lean 4 formalizations that fall
  outside Mathlib's scope. It sits between Mathlib's high-bar human
  review and "anything that compiles": projects are admitted via
  deterministic linters (no sorry/admit, no extra axioms, no
  unsafe/partial) and LLM review, and are kept building against the
  latest Mathlib. The goal is an arXiv-style index of formal-mathematics
  developments that would otherwise bit-rot in abandoned repositories.
keywords:
  - Lean
  - Lean 4
  - Mathlib
  - formal mathematics
  - formal proof
  - theorem proving
  - interactive theorem proving
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/Vilin97/lean-pool"
url: "https://vilin97.github.io/lean-pool/"
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-06-02"

# The concept DOI always resolves to the latest release; the version DOI is
# specific to v0.1.0. On each new tagged release, update the version entry.
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.20513444
identifiers:
  - type: doi
    value: 10.5281/zenodo.20513444
    description: Concept DOI resolving to the latest Lean Pool release.
  - type: doi
    value: 10.5281/zenodo.20513445
    description: DOI for the v0.1.0 release.
